Observing_System_Component.name: OSIRIS-REx
Observing_System_Component.description: Origins, Spectral Interpretation, Resource Identification, Security - Regolith Explorer Spacecraft

Field_Binary.name: ola_pwrup_counter
Field_Binary.description: Power Cycle counter. Incremented by 1 for every Power On Self Test.

Field_Binary.name: partition
Field_Binary.description: Integer that defines spacecraft clock partition employed for processing.

Field_Binary.name: t0_seconds
Field_Binary.description: Time of generation of SoH record in 32-bit seconds since 2000-01-01 00:00:00 UTC.

Field_Binary.name: t0_subseconds
Field_Binary.description: Time of generation of SoH record in subsecond counts. 1/(2**16) seconds per count.

Field_Binary.name: spare1
Field_Binary.description: Spare column

Field_Binary.name: time_ref_seconds
Field_Binary.description: Most recent time update received from spacecraft in 32-bit seconds since 2000-01-01 00:00:00 UTC.

Field_Binary.name: time_ref_subseconds
Field_Binary.description: Most recent time update in subsecond counts. 1/(2**16) seconds per count.

Field_Binary.name: spare2
Field_Binary.description: Spare column

Field_Binary.name: mrtu_ref_delta
Field_Binary.description: Time offset between OLA Time and spacecraft time per most recent time update command.

Field_Binary.name: spare3
Field_Binary.description: Spare column

Field_Binary.name: last_idp_msg_instance
Field_Binary.description: Most recent command instance received from spacecraft.

Field_Binary.name: last_idp_msg_id
Field_Binary.description: ID of most recent command instance received from spacecraft.

Field_Binary.name: cmd_exe_cnt
Field_Binary.description: Counter for the number of commands executed (excluding Time Update command).

Field_Binary.name: last_cmd_exe_instance
Field_Binary.description: Instance index of the last executed instrument command, excluding time update and noop commands.

Field_Binary.name: last_cmd_exe_id
Field_Binary.description: Command ID (IDP) of the last executed instrument command (excluding Time Update and NOOP commands).

Field_Binary.name: cmd_rjct_cnt
Field_Binary.description: Counter for the number of commands rejected.

Field_Binary.name: noop_cnt
Field_Binary.description: Number of NOOP commands received since OLA Powerup, with rollover at 65535.

Field_Binary.name: state
Field_Binary.description: Indication of state of OLA software. (1: idle, 2: standby, 3: armed, 4: operate, 5: diagnostic)

Field_Binary.name: helt_power
Field_Binary.description: HELT power status.

Field_Binary.name: lelt_power
Field_Binary.description: LELT power status. (0: off, 1: on)

Field_Binary.name: spare4
Field_Binary.description: Spare column

Field_Binary.name: current_min_range
Field_Binary.description: When scan command is active, returns the current minimum valid range.

Field_Binary.name: current_avg_range
Field_Binary.description: When scan command is active, return the average running valid range.

Field_Binary.name: msg_sent
Field_Binary.description: Count of messages sent to spacecraft, excluding state of health messages.

Field_Binary.name: duration_last_scan
Field_Binary.description: Time (duration) of last scan completed.

Field_Binary.name: time_upd_timeout
Field_Binary.description: Indication that a valid Time Update command has not been received for greater than or equal to 30 seconds. (0: no fault, 1: fault)

Field_Binary.name: time_tick_timeout
Field_Binary.description: Indication that a valid time tick has not been received for greater than or equal to 30 seconds. (0: no fault, 1: fault)

Field_Binary.name: msg_rej_wrong_block_len_msg
Field_Binary.description: Wrong block length. (0: no fault, 1: fault)

Field_Binary.name: msg_rej_bad_cmd_id

Field_Binary.name: msg_rej_bad_checksum
Field_Binary.description: Bad checksum. (0: no fault, 1: fault)

Field_Binary.name: msg_rej_invalid_cmd_data
Field_Binary.description: Invalid command data received vs ICD. (0: no fault, 1: fault)

Field_Binary.name: msg_rej_invalid_state
Field_Binary.description: Command not valid in current OLA state. (0: no fault, 1: fault)

Field_Binary.name: msg_rej_per_active_fault

Field_Binary.name: scan_buffer_overflow

Field_Binary.name: generic_sw_err
